The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, July 20, 2004 				 State heat on Centre
																								Calcutta, July 19: A CPM minister today alleged that the Manmohan Singh regime in Delhi is pursuing policies of the previous BJP-led government.																								Urban development minister Asok Bhattacharya said: They (the Centre) are trying to impose on us policies adopted by the previous government. They are surrendering to conditions laid down by funding agencies like the World Bank and the Asian Development Bank. The United Progressive Alliance government is engaging the same consultants earlier engaged by the NDA, he told the Assembly.Teacher recruitment																								The government today said it would finalise its stand on recruitment of teachers in private colleges after getting a directive from the Supreme Court. 
